        <td valign="top" width="20"><img src="../images/spacer.gif" alt="" height="20" width="20" border="0"></td>
        <td valign="top"><p class="instruct_normal"><img src="images/title_welcome.gif" alt="Welcome!" height="50" width="380" border="0"></p> <p class="instruct_normal">Welcome to Caillou's online world. This is a place where children and grown-ups can uniquely interact with their favorite four-year-old, Caillou and all his friends. There are many adventures to be had and lots of new things to learn.</p> <p class="instruct_normal">Caillou is an enjoyable way for children and grown-ups to learn together.</p> <p class="instruct_normal">Both the Caillou series and Web site encourage children to be creative while exploring the world around them.</p> <p class="instruct_normal">To read how the activities on the Caillou Web site benefit children and grown-ups, click on <a href="#GUIDE">Activity Guide.</a></p> <p class="instruct_normal">If you would like additional ideas on how to use the Caillou television series as a learning tool, click on <a href="#VIDEO">Using Video with CAILLOU</a>.</p> <p class="instruct_normal">Note: To get direct access to the game or activity, click on the game or activity title.</p> <p class="instruct_normal"><img src="images/separator_green2.gif" alt="separator" height="33" width="380" border="0"></p> <p class="Song_text_bold"><a name="GUIDE"></a><img src="images/title_activityguide.gif" alt="Activity Guide" height="50" width="380" border="0"></p> <p class="grownups_bold_red"><a href="../games/stars.html"><img src="images/sub_stars.gif" alt="Follow the Stars" height="26" width="300" border="0"></a></p>
         <blockquote>
          <p class="activiity_desc">The stars in the sky blink in a certain sequence. The child has to repeat this sequence by clicking on each star in the same order. The number of blinks in each of the three levels is limited so that the children can practice and become better gradually.<br></p>
          <p class="activiity_desc"><font color="#00af4c">Educational Benefit:</font><br> This game helps young children with their concentration skills. Brightly colored and illustrated with fun sounds, this game can also help the child with hand-eye coordination.</p>
          <p class="footer_nav"><a href="#TOP">top of page</a></p>
         </blockquote> <p class="instruct_normal">&nbsp;</p> <p class="grownups_bold_red"><a href="../games/puzzle.html"><img src="images/sub_puzzle.gif" alt="Puzzle Game" height="26" width="300" border="0"></a></p>
         <blockquote>
          <p class="activiity_desc">Jigsaw puzzles have almost always been a favorite game for children and grownups alike. Four different puzzles are offered featuring Caillou along with family and friends. There are two levels of "difficulty": 9-piece puzzles and 12-piece puzzles. To help kids solve the puzzles, you can also show the semi-transparent representation of the final assembled puzzle.<br></p>
          <p class="activiity_desc"><font color="#00af4c">Educational Benefit:</font><br> Helps children match shapes and colors.</p>
          <p class="footer_nav"><a href="#TOP">top of page</a></p>
         </blockquote> <p class="instruct_normal">&nbsp;</p> <p class="grownups_bold_red"><a href="../games/spelling.html"><img src="images/sub_spell.gif" alt="Spelling with Caillou" height="26" width="300" border="0"></a></p>
         <blockquote>
          <p class="activiity_desc">This spelling game can be played by young children even if they do not know yet how to read. Using the familiar sounding names of the Caillou series characters, the child will try to match the letters found on play blocks with the letters appearing at the top of the frame. The children choose the word to spell by clicking on the word itself or on the picture representing the character in question.<br></p>
          <p class="activiity_desc"><font color="#00af4c">Educational Benefit:</font><br> Helps the children familiarize themselves with the different shapes of the letters of the alphabet.</p>
          <p class="footer_nav"><a href="#TOP">top of page</a></p>
         </blockquote> <p class="instruct_normal">&nbsp;</p> <p class="grownups_bold_red"><a href="../games/memory.html"><img src="images/sub_memory.gif" alt="Memory Game" height="26" width="300" border="0"></a></p>
         <blockquote>
          <p class="activiity_desc">This is a fun card game children can play alone, with friends or with a grown-up. Children click on the cards that are turned over and try to remember the drawing on it. Then they try to find its match by clicking on the other cards.<br></p>
          <p class="activiity_desc"><font color="#00af4c">Educational Benefit:</font><br> This fun game helps children develop short and long term memory skills.</p>
          <p class="footer_nav"><a href="#TOP">top of page</a></p>
         </blockquote> <p class="instruct_normal">&nbsp;</p> <p class="grownups_bold_red"><a href="../games/matching.html"><img src="images/sub_match.gif" alt="Matching Game" height="26" width="300" border="0"></a></p>
         <blockquote>
          <p class="activiity_desc">The object of this game is for the child to try to match different shapes and colors together. Easy and fun, the child gets immediate gratification when he/she finds the identical shape and color.<br></p>
          <p class="activiity_desc"><font color="#00af4c">Educational Benefit:</font><br> Helps the child develop his/her sense of observation by trying to discern the differences between members of the same family of objects. No two butterflies or leaves are exactly alike.</p>
          <p class="footer_nav"><a href="#TOP">top of page</a></p>
         </blockquote> <p class="instruct_normal">&nbsp;</p> <p class="grownups_bold_red"><a href="../activities/paint.html"><img src="images/sub_paint.gif" alt="Painting Activity" height="26" width="300" border="0"></a></p>
         <blockquote>
          <p class="activiity_desc">Children love to paint! Here they get their chance to use their imaginations and creativity skills. Children can choose different colors to paint Caillou shown in different activities and poses. They can paint however they want and can start over at any time. Just for the fun of it!<br></p>
          <p class="activiity_desc"><font color="#00af4c">Educational Benefit:</font><br> This activity helps children differentiate between different colors and also helps them acquire more dexterity by using the mouse to color Caillou, all while fostering their creative and expressive interests.</p>
          <p class="footer_nav"><a href="#TOP">top of page</a></p>
         </blockquote> <p class="instruct_normal">&nbsp;</p> <p class="grownups_bold_red"><a href="../activities/dots.html"><img src="images/sub_dots.gif" alt="Connect the Dots" height="26" width="300" border="0"></a></p>
         <blockquote>
          <p class="activiity_desc">This is a printable activity where children can draw and color while learning the alphabet and numbers. This game can be played with friends, or, makes an ideal learning opportunity with the guidance of a parent/educator who can help the child to trace the outline of the drawing while reciting the alphabet in the correct order.<br></p>
          <p class="activiity_desc"><font color="#00af4c">Educational Benefit:</font><br> A fun activity that combines many things a child loves: coloring, drawing and reciting. Helps the child understand that things come in a certain order and assists the child in learning the letters of the alphabet. Great activity to do with a caregiver or educator.</p>
          <p class="footer_nav"><a href="#TOP">top of page</a></p>
         </blockquote> <p class="instruct_normal">&nbsp;</p> <p class="grownups_bold_red"><a href="../activities/paint.html"><img src="images/sub_memory_act.gif" alt="Memory Game Activity" height="26" width="300" border="0"></a></p>
         <blockquote>
          <p class="activiity_desc">This activity is the printed version of the electronic Memory Game found on the Caillou website. This enables the child to play this game other than on the computer. The child can print this activity, play at it home, at a friend's house, at grandma's and grandpa's, in the car during travel, etc.<br></p>
          <p class="activiity_desc"><font color="#00af4c">Educational Benefit:</font><br> This activity will require the participation of an parent or educator. It assists the child in the development of team work by splitting the different tasks to perform: the child can do all the coloring while the parent or educator does the cutting, for example.</p>
          <p class="footer_nav"><a href="#TOP">top of page</a></p>
         </blockquote> <p class="instruct_normal">&nbsp;</p> <p class="grownups_bold_red"><a href="../games/dresscaillou.html"><img src="images/sub_dresscaillou.gif" alt="Dress Caillou" height="26" width="300" border="0"></a></p>
         <blockquote>
          <p class="activiity_desc">Dress Caillou is designed to help children understand how to pick appropriate outfits based on the weather outside. Children first look outside Caillou's window to see what the weather is like. Then, they must select a suitable outfit by using their mouse so that Caillou can go outside and play.<br></p>
          <p class="activiity_desc"><font color="#00af4c">Educational Benefit:</font><br> This game will help children improve their ability to use a computer mouse, identify links on Web sites, as well as associate the different types of weather with different articles of clothing.</p>
          <p class="footer_nav"><a href="#TOP">top of page</a></p>
         </blockquote> <p class="instruct_normal">&nbsp;</p> <p class="grownups_bold_red"><a href="../activities/paperdolls.html"><img src="images/sub_paperdolls.gif" alt="Paper Dolls" height="26" width="300" border="0"></a></p>
         <blockquote>
          <p class="activiity_desc">Caillou's Paper Dolls is an activity that lets children color three different Caillou outfits, using crayons or markers. With help from a grown-up, children can then cut out the outfits and dress the Caillou paper doll. Another activity children can play is to dress Caillou appropriately for the weather they see outside their own window. Or, a grown-up could name a season and the child would have to select the appropriate Caillou outfit.<br></p>
          <p class="activiity_desc"><font color="#00af4c">Educational Benefit:</font><br> Children will learn how to dress appropriately for different types of weather. They will also be practicing hand control and how to use scissors safely.</p>
          <p class="footer_nav"><a href="#TOP">top of page</a></p>
         </blockquote> <p class="instruct_normal">&nbsp;</p> <p class="grownups_bold_red"><a href="../games/searching.html"><img src="images/sub_searching.gif" alt="Find Gilbert" height="26" width="300" border="0"></a></p>
         <blockquote>
          <p class="activiity_desc">Find Gilbert is a game that teaches children how to search for and recognize familiar objects. This is an excellent way for children to learn how to recognize objects without seeing them in their entirety. The child uses their mouse to locate Gilbert, Teddy or Rexy. Hidden in the scene are also other surprises to find using the mouse.<br></p>
          <p class="activiity_desc"><font color="#00af4c">Educational Benefit:</font><br> Learning how to recognize objects without seeing them in their entirety is the object of this game. Children will also use the mouse to explore the scene for other links, an important tool to learn prior to learning how to use the Internet.</p>
          <p class="footer_nav"><a href="#TOP">top of page</a></p>
         </blockquote> <p class="instruct_normal">&nbsp;</p> <p class="grownups_bold_red"><a href="../games/keyboard.html"><img src="images/sub_keyboard.gif" alt="The Magic Keyboard" height="26" width="300" border="0"></a></p>
         <blockquote>
          <p class="activiity_desc">Magic Keyboard is designed to be a fun way to encourage children to use the computer keyboard. Each letter the child types has a distinctive sound. Learning to type is fun while making music. Children can also click on Caillou, Gilbert, Teddy or Rexy to see how their names are spelled and to hear how they sound.<br></p>
          <p class="activiity_desc"><font color="#00af4c">Educational Benefit:</font><br> The majority of Internet navigation is done with a mouse. It is important that children also have exposure to keyboard use, Magic Keyboard does just that.</p>
          <p class="footer_nav"><a href="#TOP">top of page</a></p>
         </blockquote> <p class="instruct_normal">&nbsp;</p> <p class="grownups_bold_red"><a href="../activities/storybook.html"><img src="images/sub_storybook.gif" alt="Picture Storybook" height="26" width="300" border="0"></a></p>
         <blockquote>
          <p class="activiity_desc">The Picture Storybook is a book that children can color with crayons or markers. At the bottom of each page is a section where children can either write or draw their own story. With the help of a grown-up the pages are cut out along the lines and holes are punched into the marked areas. Children are encouraged to be creative when placing the pictures in order. However, there are a few pictures that could be placed in sequence, if the child chooses to do so. Once picture order is established, children can use string or ribbon to lace through the holes to tie the book together.<br></p>
          <p class="activiity_desc"><font color="#00af4c">Educational Benefit:</font><br> This activity will help children improve their coloring, cutting and writing skills as well as encouraging children to be creative while inventing their own story.</p>
          <p class="footer_nav"><a href="#TOP">top of page</a></p>
         </blockquote> <p class="instruct_normal">&nbsp;</p> <p class="grownups_bold_red"><a href="../activities/coloringbook.html"><img src="images/sub_coloringbook.gif" alt="Coloring Pages" height="26" width="300" border="0"></a></p>
         <blockquote>
          <p class="activiity_desc">The Coloring Pages are designed to help children with hand control while they color Caillou and other characters. Children can use crayons or markers to color in the pictures.<br></p>
          <p class="activiity_desc"><font color="#00af4c">Educational Benefit:</font><br> Practicing hand control is fun while coloring the pictures.</p>
          <p class="footer_nav"><a href="#TOP">top of page</a></p>
         </blockquote> <p class="instruct_normal">&nbsp;</p> <p class="grownups_bold_red"><a href="cooking.html"><img src="images/sub_cook.gif" alt="Cook with Caillou" height="26" width="300" border="0"></a></p>
         <blockquote>
          <p class="activiity_desc">The recipes are designed to give children an introduction to cooking. Grown-ups and children will have lots of fun while making these delicious creations.<br></p>
          <p class="activiity_desc"><font color="#00af4c">Educational Benefit:</font><br> Children can learn how different ingredients are mixed together to make something new, while learning how to measure and how to follow a recipe.</p>
          <p class="footer_nav"><a href="#TOP">top of page</a></p>
         </blockquote> <p class="instruct_normal">&nbsp;</p> <p class="grownups_bold_red"><a href="../activities/paint.html"><img src="images/sub_singalong.gif" alt="Sing Along with Caillou" height="26" width="300" border="0"></a></p>
         <blockquote>
          <p class="activiity_desc">Children sing along to their favorite songs while seeing the words in front of them.<br></p>
          <p class="activiity_desc"><font color="#00af4c">Educational Benefit:</font><br> The Sing Along is a fun way for children to learn word recognition, and some introductory reading skills.</p>
          <p class="footer_nav"><a href="#TOP">top of page</a></p>
         </blockquote> <p class="instruct_normal"><img src="images/separator_green2.gif" alt="separator" height="33" width="380" border="0"></p> <p class="grownups_title"><a name="VIDEO"></a><font color="#ed1c24">Using Video with CAILLOU</font></p> <p class="instruct_normal">Make the most of CAILLOU, before, during and after! Use these television tips to get the most fun and learning out of the series. And don't forget -- it's a show everyone can watch together!</p>
         <dl>
          <dt class="grownups_bold_blue">
           <font color="#0077c0">Before CAILLOU airs: </font>
          </dt>
         </dl>
         <ul>
          <li type="disc" class="instruct_normal">Review the episode description, or if you have access, view the episode so you are familiar with the stories.</li>
          <li type="disc" class="instruct_normal">Make sure everyone watching the program has a comfortable seat.</li>
          <li type="disc" class="instruct_normal">Talk with the children about what they might see. Imaginations are wonderful!</li>
         </ul>
         <dl>
          <dt class="grownups_bold_blue">
           <font color="#0077c0">During the CAILLOU episode: </font>
          </dt>
         </dl>
         <ul>
          <li type="disc" class="instruct_normal">Keep the lights on, but pull shades to reduce glare.</li>
          <li type="disc" class="instruct_normal">Observe the childrens' reactions - When do they laugh? What are they reacting to?</li>
         </ul>
         <dl>
          <dt class="grownups_bold_blue">
           <font color="#0077c0">After CAILLOU is over: </font>
          </dt>
         </dl>
         <ul>
          <li type="disc" class="instruct_normal">Ask the children to describe their favorite parts.</li>
          <li type="disc" class="instruct_normal">Talk with the children about the theme of the day.</li>
          <li type="disc" class="instruct_normal">Help the children pick out related books, or play a related game.</li>
          <li type="disc" class="instruct_normal">Use the materials in the topic areas for additional skill building and reinforcement.</li>
         </ul>
         <dl>
          <dt class="grownups_bold_blue">
           <font color="#0077c0">Especially for Trainers and Teachers: </font>
          </dt>
         </dl>
         <ul>
          <li type="disc" class="instruct_normal">More Ways to Incorporate CAILLOU Video into Programs</li>
